# Playwright Installation

1️⃣ Introduction
Playwright is a tool used to End to End(E2E) testing of web applications.
It allows tests to automate browsers and test web applications automatically.
Features
--------
    1. Supports multiple browsers
        -> Chrome
        -> WebKit
        -> FireFox
    2. Works on different OS
        -> Windows
        -> Linux
        -> MacOS
    3. Can run tests
        -> Headless mode (without browser UI)
        -> Headed mode (with browser UI)

    4. Supports native mobile emulation
    5. Can run in locally or in CI/CD pipelines

2️⃣ Playwright Library
The playwright library is used for browser automation.
It provides powerful APIs to automate web applications.
Playwright supports TWO types of execution styles.
--------------------------------------------------
    1. sync API
    2. async API

These APIs help interact with browsers and perform actions like:
----------------------------------------------------------------
    1. Opening browsers
    2. Clicking buttons
    3. Submitting forms
    4. Validating results

3️⃣ Playwright Pytest Plugin
Playwright recommands using the "Playwright Pytest Plugin" for writting tests.
Plugin Name
-----------
    pytest-playwright

Why use this plugin?
--------------------
It provides:
    1. Context Isolation
    2. Easy browser setup
    3. Multiple browser testing
    4. Integration with pytest

